{
  "stem": "7455.2",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "From the anxiety, from the fear, in a few days, we lost weight from not-- not from not eating-- from the fear.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And after a few days, the Russians were retreating.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The bombing stopped, and the Germans were marching in.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we hear-- the earth was shaking because the highway was not far.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And as the Germans went forward, the Germans occu-- began to occupy Brody.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "For the Germ-- for the Ukrainian, it was time to have a celebration in church.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So we had to vacant, vacant out the church and go out.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And they are cleaning up the church.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Our neighbors who did not have their homes, they had other Ukrainians who came and invited them to their homes.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And they knew it's going to even be better because they'll-- they're victims.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Maybe they'll give them the most beautiful home of the Jews, even though their home was nice.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "We came out with our bundles and looked at the ruins of our house, still smoldering, still that stench of smoke.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Our beautiful garden-- leaves were shriveled up, the ones that were closer to the house.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Further down, deeper in the garden, it didn't burn down.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Still traces of our-- the fence burned down.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "That little house in the garden, underneath it, we had also a cement cellar where we used to storage the food on the shelves.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And it was a cooler.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "You walked down-- you-- in that little house, you lifted the floor, a door.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "It went down to a cemented cellar, where we-- all our foods, and butter and milk-- we had no refrigeration in those years.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "Even our tenants were allowed to do it.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "Only the steps were there, the cement steps.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "The whole-- that beautiful little, like gingerbread house, was gone.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
